A quadratic has exactly one real root if and only if its discriminant is zero.  The discriminant of the quadratic $x^2+4mx+m$ is $(4m)^2-4m=\boxed{16}m^2-4m$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

real g(real x) {
  return(x^2 + 8*x + 7);
}

draw(graph(g,-16,8),red);
draw((-16,0)--(8,0));
draw((0,-5)--(0,35));

label("$y = x^2 + 4mx + m$", (10,0), S, red);
[/asy]
